 aspects of Serreau's films and plays, are thoroughly examined. This book also considers the cultural influences of her work, and provides an overview of her films and filmic skills. Special attention is given to comedy, the cinematographic genre favoured by Serreau and the French audience, which is apprehended from a historical and gendered perspective. The clarity of the style and the wide-ranging analysis of Serreau's films and filming techniques make this book relevant both to students of film and film enthusiasts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directors. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh  aColine Serreau.  aFrench cinema.  aFrench comedies.  aUtopian mood.  acinematographic genres.  afemale French director.  afemale humour.  afemale laughter.  afiction.  aliterary influence.  atheatre.  atransgressive laughter.1 aRollet, Brigitte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614205440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526142054423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526142054/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles